hands_on_practices.solution:
Consider a macroscopic volume $V$ at radius $r$.  The total mass in $V$ is
$$m_{\rm tot}
=V\bigl(f_V\rho_{cl}+(1-f_V)\rho_{ic}\bigr)
=V\rho_{ic}\bigl(\chi f_V+(1-f_V)\bigr)\,. $$
Each clump (radius $R_{cl}$) has mass 
$$m_{cl}=\tfrac{4}{3}\pi R_{cl}^3\rho_{cl}\,, $$
and mean column density
$$\bar\Sigma_{cl}=\frac{m_{cl}}{\pi R_{cl}^2}
=\frac{\tfrac{4}{3}\pi R_{cl}^3\rho_{cl}}{\pi R_{cl}^2}
=\tfrac{4}{3}\rho_{cl}R_{cl}\,\;\Rightarrow\;R_{cl}=\frac{3\bar\Sigma_{cl}}{4\rho_{cl}}\,. $$
The number of clumps in $V$ is $N_{cl}=f_VV/V_{cl}=f_VV/(\tfrac{4}{3}\pi R_{cl}^3)$, so the total geometric cross­section is
$$\Sigma_{\rm tot}
=N_{cl}\,\pi R_{cl}^2
=\frac{f_VV\,\pi R_{cl}^2}{\tfrac{4}{3}\pi R_{cl}^3}
=f_VV\,\frac{3}{4R_{cl}}
=f_VV\,\frac{\rho_{cl}}{\bar\Sigma_{cl}}\,. $$
Hence the outward radiative force on $V$ is
$$F_{\rm rad}
=\frac{L}{4\pi r^2c}\,\Sigma_{\rm tot}
=\frac{L}{4\pi r^2c}\,f_VV\frac{\rho_{cl}}{\bar\Sigma_{cl}}\,. $$
The mean radiative acceleration is
$$a_{\rm rad}
=\frac{F_{\rm rad}}{m_{\rm tot}}
=\frac{L}{4\pi r^2c}\,
\frac{f_V\rho_{cl}/\bar\Sigma_{cl}}
{\rho_{ic}(\chi f_V+(1-f_V))} 
=\frac{L}{4\pi r^2c}\,
\frac{f_V\chi}
{\bar\Sigma_{cl}(\chi f_V+1-f_V)}\,. $$
Balance $a_{\rm rad}=g=GM/r^2$ to find $L_{Edd,\,eff}$:
$$\frac{L_{Edd,eff}}{4\pi r^2c}
\frac{f_V\chi}
{\bar\Sigma_{cl}(\chi f_V+1-f_V)}
=\frac{GM}{r^2}
\;\;\Rightarrow\;\;
L_{Edd,eff}
=4\pi GMc\,\bar\Sigma_{cl}\,
\frac{\chi f_V+1-f_V}{f_V\chi}
=4\pi GMc\,\bar\Sigma_{cl}\,
\frac{1+f_V(\chi-1)}{f_V\chi}\,. $$
